The Court of Arbitration for Sport has lifted Morocco's ban from the next two editions of the African Cup of Nations that was imposed by the Confederation of African Football.

The North-African nation was expelled from the 2017 and 2019 tournaments and was fined $1 million by the CAF. 

The CAF also demanded a further $9 million in compensation, after the country pulled out because of fears related to the Ebola epidemic.

