CAS said that the sanctions have been set aside, 'with the exception of the fine, which is however reduced to $50,000.'

Morocco was disqualified from this year's tournament after withdrawing as host just two months before the start of the competition. 

Their national federation cited health risks from fans travelling from Ebola-affected regions. 

It asked for a delay but CAF refused and the tournament was moved to Equatorial Guinea.

 

